					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12838506#post-4441393</guid>
				<title>+1</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12838506/scp-4026#post-4441393</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 08 Dec 2019 20:50:52 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>MemeFury</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4001485</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>At first I thought this was gonna be a 4999-esqe article, what with the &quot;right before death&quot; setting and the mysterious entity, and while it was made better by the fact the thing spites people out of actually killing themselves (regardless of that's even its intention), it still wouldn't have made this a solid SCP.</p> <p>That is, until it gets into its neutralization.</p> <p>Damn I love irony.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12838506#post-4438222</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12838506/scp-4026#post-4438222</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 04 Dec 2019 15:47:32 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Rioghail</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1302192</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I thought I was going to downvote this when I started, but the twist completely won me over. Personally, I love the fact that Schneider accidentally killed the anomaly; it definitely makes the piece's ending abrupt and off-kilter, but honestly I thought that just made the whole thing funnier. I can just see the camera freeze-framing on Schneider's expression of shock after he yeets the dickhead angel off the cliff as the credits start rolling.</p> <p>I would say that, given the extremely widespread exposure of Beachy Head as a suicide location, I feel like some lip service to that high public profile in the description is probably warranted, just for a suspension of disbelief.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
